The paper deals with domain adaptation in the context of image classification, which is a problem commonly studied in the computer vision community (cs.CV). The proposed method involves designing a latent feature representation that minimizes the discrepancy between the source and target domains, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of label propagation and label smoothness constraints, which are techniques commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves designing a repulsive force term to increase the discriminative power of the adapted domain, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
